The paper deals with the design and analysis of a new certificateless ring signature scheme, which involves cryptographic primitives such as random oracles, Computational Diffie-Hellman problem, and security models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves some aspects of computational complexity and information theory, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely categories as well. The paper proposes a concrete scheme, which involves some implementation aspects, making cs.CE (Computers and Society) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the security of the proposed scheme, which involves formalizing security models and analyzing the scheme's vulnerability to attacks, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category.
